The  Carlyle Group  is favorite to buy
Spanish cable operator Telecable, beating offers by  CVC Capital
Partners  and Grupo ONO,  Expansion  reported, citing unidentified
people with knowledge of the matter.                    Carlyle
will offer around 400 million euros ($551.1 million) for the
company, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
